Arthur Fitzhardinge Kingscote (12 July 1841 – 5 February 1881) was an English cricketer.  Kingscote was born at Westminster in London.
Kingscote played three first-class matches for the Marylebone Cricket Club from 1858 to 1859.  He made his first-class debut against Cambridge University and played two further fixtures for the club against the same opposition and against the Gentlemen of Kent.Kingscote died at Fulham, London on 5 February 1881.
